8) Recommended Run & Troubleshooting Steps
- Prerequisites: Node.js >= 24.0.0, npm installed.
- Install dependencies: npm ci or npm install
- Run tests locally: npm test (unit) or npm run test:unit for coverage
- If vitest fails to start: ensure Node >=24 and reinstall node_modules (rm -rf node_modules package-lock.json && npm ci).
- If a script prints "Nothing to build" that indicates intentionally empty build step; no build artifacts expected.
- For failing unit tests: run vitest with --reporter verbose by invoking directly: npx vitest --run tests/unit/*.test.js --reporter verbose

